description.p:
The following is provided:
1. A receptor activator of NF-κB ligand (RANKL) antibody - parathyroid hormone/parathyroid hormone related protein (PTH/PTHrP) chimeric molecule, comprising:
(a) an antibody that binds to RANKL; and
(b) a first PTH/PTHrP peptide; wherein the PTH/PTHrP peptide is covalently linked to the antibody, and wherein the RANKL antibody-PTH/PTHrP chimeric molecule (i) inhibits binding of RANKL to a receptor activator of NF-κB (RANK) and (ii) binds to a PTH-1 receptor and/or a PTH-2 receptor.
2. The RANKL antibody-PTH/PTHrP chimeric molecule of 1, wherein the antibody that binds to RANKL comprises a heavy chain and a light chain, wherein the heavy chain comprises an amino acid sequence that has at least 92% identity to the amino acid sequence set forth in SEQ ID NO: 11.
3. The RANKL antibody-PTH/PTHrP chimeric molecule of 1 or 2, wherein the antibody that binds to RANKL comprises a heavy chain and a light chain, wherein the light chain comprises an amino acid sequence that has at least 90% identity to the amino acid sequence set forth in SEQ ID NO: 12.
4. The RANKL antibody-PTH/PTHrP chimeric molecule of any of 1 to 3, wherein the antibody that binds to RANKL comprises a heavy chain and a light chain, wherein the heavy chain comprises an amino acid sequence that has at least 95% identity to the amino acid sequence set forth in SEQ ID NO: 11.
5. The RANKL antibody-PTH/PTHrP chimeric molecule of any of 1 to 4, wherein the antibody that binds to RANKL comprises a heavy chain and a light chain, wherein the light chain comprises an amino acid sequence that has at least 95% identity to the amino acid sequence set forth in SEQ ID NO: 12.
6. The RANKL antibody-PTH/PTHrP chimeric molecule of any of 1 to 5, wherein the antibody that binds to RANKL comprises a heavy chain and a light chain, wherein the heavy chain comprises an amino acid sequence that has at least 99% identity to the amino acid sequence set forth in SEQ ID NO: 11.
7. The RANKL antibody-PTH/PTHrP chimeric molecule of any of 1 to 6, wherein the antibody that binds to RANKL comprises a heavy chain and a light chain, wherein the light chain comprises an amino acid sequence that has at least 99% identity to the amino acid sequence set forth in SEQ ID NO: 12.
8. The RANKL antibody-PTH/PTHrP chimeric molecule of any of 1 to 7, wherein the antibody that binds to RANKL comprises a heavy chain and a light chain, wherein the heavy chain comprises an amino acid sequence as set forth in SEQ ID NO: 11.
9. The RANKL antibody-PTH/PTHrP chimeric molecule of any of 1 to 8, wherein the antibody that binds to RANKL comprises a heavy chain and a light chain, wherein the light chain comprises an amino acid sequence as set forth in SEQ ID NO: 12.
10. The RANKL antibody-PTH/PTHrP chimeric molecule of 1 wherein the antibody comprises a heavy chain and a light chain, and wherein the heavy chain comprises an amino acid sequence as set forth in SEQ ID NO: 2 from residue 20 to residue 427, and the light chain comprises an amino acid sequence as set forth in SEQ ID NO: 4 from residue 21 to residue 235.
11. The RANKL antibody-PTH/PTHrP chimeric molecule of any of 1 to 10, wherein the first PTH/PTHrP peptide comprises a prepro domain and a PTH/PTHrP modulating domain that binds to a PTH-1 receptor and/or a PTH-2 receptor.
12. The RANKL antibody-PTH/PTHrP chimeric molecule of any of 1 to 10, wherein the first PTH/PTHrP peptide is covalently linked to a heavy chain.
13. The RANKL antibody-PTH/PTHrP chimeric molecule of any of 1 to 10, wherein the first PTH/PTHrP peptide is covalently linked to a light chain.
14. The RANKL antibody-PTH/PTHrP chimeric molecule of any of 1 to 9, wherein the antibody is selected from a single-chain Fv antibody (scFv), a Fab antibody, a Fab' antibody, a (Fab')2 antibody, a domain antibody, a nanobody, a minibody, a maxibody, and a diabody.
15. The RANKL antibody-PTH/PTHrP chimeric molecule of any of 1 to 10, further comprising a second PTH/PTHrP peptide, wherein the first and second PTH/PTHrP peptides are the same or different.
16. The RANKL antibody-PTH/PTHrP chimeric molecule of 14, wherein the second PTH/PTHrP peptide comprises a prepro domain and a PTH/PTHrP modulating domain.
17. The RANKL antibody-PTH/PTHrP chimeric molecule of 14, wherein the the antibody that binds to RANKL comprises a heavy chain and a light chain, and wherein the first PTH/PTHrP peptide is covalently linked to the light chain and the second PTH/PTHrP peptide is covalently linked to the heavy chain.
18. The RANKL antibody-PTH/PTHrP chimeric molecule of any of 1 to 10, wherein the antibody is fully human.
19. The RANKL antibody-PTH/PTHrP chimeric molecule of any of 1 to 17, wherein the first and/or second PTH/PTHrP peptide comprises a PTH/PTHrP modulating domain selected from the polypeptides of formula I:
